==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Merry-go-round
<hw>Mer"ry-go`-round"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Any
revolving contrivance for affording amusement; esp., a group of seats in
the shape of hobbyhorses or other fanciful animals, arranged in a circle
on a platform that is rotated by a mechanical drive, often to the
accompaniment of music; the seats often move up and down in synchrony
with the rotation; -- called also <altname>carousel</altname>. It is
employed primarily for the amusement of children, and is typically found
at an amusement park.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Merrymake</ent>⟦br⟧
